Aim:
To learn how to use control flow statements and looping statements in Python.

Algorithm:
Start the program.
Ask the user to enter a number.
Use an if–else statement to check whether the number is even or odd.
Use a for loop to print numbers from 1 to 5.
Use a while loop to print numbers from 1 to the entered number.
Display all the results.
End the program.

Code:
num = int(input("Enter a number: "))
if num % 2 == 0:
    print("The number is Even")
else:
    print("The number is Odd")
print("Numbers from 1 to 5 using for loop:")
for i in range(1, 6):
    print(i)
print("Numbers from 1 to", num, "using while loop:")
i = 1
while i <= num:
    print(i)
    i += 1

